comments: Collins (SAS) maintains verticality as he is absorbing the contact initiated by Jackson Jr. (MEM) while contesting Jackson Jr.'s shot attempt at the rim.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of an offensive goaltending on Jackson Jr. (MEM) is overturned.  Jackson Jr. makes contact with the ball when it is outside of the imaginary cylinder above the basket ring.
Branham (SAS) grazes Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) arm during the dunk and the contact is marginal.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) reaches in and makes clean contact with the ball.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) firms up in Vassell's (SAS) path and incidental contact occurs as the pick is set.
Collins (SAS) initiates leg to leg contact with Jones (MEM), which dislodges him from his defensive position.
Collins (SAS) receives a technical foul after engaging in a verbal altercation with Brooks (MEM).
Brooks (MEM) receives a technical foul after engaging in a verbal altercation with Collins (SAS).
Jackson Jr. (MEM) and Jones (SAS) come together and incidental contact occurs as the pick is set.
Brooks (MEM) briefly grasps Johnson's  (SAS) arm and immediately releases it as the screen is set.
Collins (SAS) firms up in Bane's (MEM) path and absorbs the contact.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) rests his hand on Collins' (SAS) front and marginal contact occurs as Collins is running through the lane.
Collins (SAS) turns his hip in Jackson Jr. (MEM) and delivers contact, affecting Jackson Jr.'s ability to contest the layup.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) establishes himself in Jones' (SAS) path and incidental contact occurs as the pick is set.
Collins (SAS) maintains a legal guarding position defending Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Vassell (SAS) makes contact with the ball as he reaches for the rebound and any contact with Jackson Jr. (MEM) is incidental.
Brooks (MEM) establishes a screening position and does not deliver illegal contact to Collins (SAS).
SAS is awarded a timeout before any possible illegal contact by Jones (SAS).
Jackson Jr.'s (MEM) hand slides off of Collins' (SAS) arm and marginal contact occurs prior to the held ball.
Bane (MEM) avoids making contact with Vassell (SAS) as he is contesting the jump shot.
Jones (SAS) moves alongside Jones' (MEM) path and maintains a legal guarding position while contesting the driving shot attempt.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) extends his arm into Jones (SAS) and initiates contact that affects his driving shot attempt.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) firms up in Vassell's (SAS) path and incidental contact occurs as the pick is set.
Bane (MEM) slightly extends his arm into Branham (SAS) as the pick is set.
Johnson (SAS) gets a hand on the ball and incidental body contact occurs with Kennard (MEM) as both players pursue the loose ball.
Brooks (MEM) places a forearm against Jones's (SAS) back and the contact is marginal.
Collins (SAS) is in the lane for longer than three seconds.
Jones (MEM) releases without dislodging Jones (MEM) from his defensive position after the two players briefly engage and disengage.
Correctly called 24 second violation.
Johnson (SAS) commits a take foul on Brooks (MEM).
Johnson (SAS) initiates contact with Jones' (MEM) arm which affects his ability to pass the ball on the perimeter.
Kennard (MEM) briefly grasps Branham's (SAS) arm as both players are positioning themselves to receive the rebound.
Johnson (SAS) extends a leg towards Brooks (MEM) to create contact, but the contact is marginal.
